					<physDesc rend="visible">
						<p>Parchment codex of the 14th century.</p>
						<objectDesc form="codex">
							<supportDesc material="perg">
								<extent>233 folios <dimensions unit="mm" type="leaf">
										<height>317</height>
										<width>220</width>
									</dimensions>
									<dimensions type="written" unit="mm">
										<height>166</height>
										<width>116</width>
									</dimensions>
								</extent>
								<foliation>
									<p>233 folios (+ 4 modern paper flyleaves at the beginning and 3 at the end).  </p>
								</foliation>
								<collation>
									<p>Originally 25 quires (23 complete extant): i-ii? (folios missing), iii-ix10 (folios 1-70), x8 (folios 71-78), xi-xx10 (folios 79-188), xxi12 (folios 189-200), xxii10 (folios 201-210), xxiii8 (folios 211-218), xxiv4 (folios 229-233). Quires marked with catchwords at the end. </p>
								</collation>
							</supportDesc>
							<layoutDesc>
								<layout columns="1 " ruledLines="31" writtenLines="30">
									<p>Uniform layout. </p>
									<p>Visible pricking and hard-point ruling (also in the margins, which have been left blank). </p>
									<p>Last line of writing written within the ruling. </p>
									<p>Hair side and flesh side of folios distinguishable. </p>
									<p>Occasional marginal notes. </p>
								</layout>
							</layoutDesc>
						</objectDesc>
						<handDesc hands="1">
							<summary>Italian semi-cursive script of approximately 14th century.</summary>
							<handNote script="Hebrew" scope="sole"/>
						</handDesc>
						<additions>
							<p>Folio 233v - a doodle page.</p>
							<p>
								<name type="person" role="owner">Yosef Dinah</name>: inscribed, folio 233r. </p>
							<p>Censored by <name type="person" role="censor">Domenico Irosolimitano</name>, Italian censor (active in the last quarter of the 16th and first quarter of the 17th century): inscribed with his name, 1600 (folio 232v); see <ref target="Popper_1969" type="page">61</ref>, and appendix § 62-74.
 </p>
							<p>Censored by <name type="person" role="censor">Giovanni Domenico Carretto</name>, Italian censor (active in the first quarter of the 17th century): inscribed with his name, 1628 (folio 214v); see <ref target="Popper_1969" type="page">100-101</ref>, and appendix § 80-84. </p>
						</additions>
						<bindingDesc>
							<binding>
								<p>Post-1600. Dark brown leather, with gold-tooled Harleian coat of arms.</p>
								<p>Spine title: 'Isaac b. Jacob Alfasi. Halakhoth. Hebrew. Brit. Mus. Harley Ms. 5705.'</p>
							</binding>
